CMake variables that may be of interest
=======================================

CMAKE_MODULE_PATH

	Specifies the path where cmake can find the additional
	modules that the OpenSync build process requires.
	You can download the modules here:
		http://repo.or.cz/w/opensync/cmake-modules-cdf.git

CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX

	Specifies where 'make install' will install the resulting
	libraries, binaries, and header files.

CMAKE_C_COMPILER:STRING=/usr/local/bin/ccache_gcc

	Specifies the path to find your desired C compiler

CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER:STRING=/usr/local/bin/ccache_g++

	Specifies the path to find your desired C++ compiler

CMAKE_C_FLAGS:STRING="-Wall -Werror -O0 -fno-strict-aliasing"

	Specifies C compiler flags

CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS:STRING="-Wall -Werror -O0 -fno-strict-aliasing"

	Specifies C++ compiler flags

CMAKE_C_FLAGS_RELWITHDEBINFO:STRING="-g"

	Enable debug info in (release?) builds.

CMAKE_VERBOSE_MAKEFILE:BOOL=TRUE

	Enables verbose makefile messages

CMAKE_SKIP_RPATH:BOOL=TRUE

	Turns off RPATH from all resulting binaries.

BUILD_DOCUMENTATION:BOOL=ON

	When on, it adds an extra make target: make DoxygenDoc

